programme.title: Winchester Deadly Passion
programme.desc: Summer is the ideal time to hit the water and spend some quality time bowfishing, but Melissa takes it up a notch by going after everything from tuna to shark to alligator gar.(n)

programme.title: Relentless Pursuit
programme.desc: Sydnie Wells goes deep into the flooded timber for monster grassies while Brother Buck & Tim blowgun gar in the southern back water.(n)

programme.title: Sporting Chef
programme.desc: Chef Scott gives his take on how to best handle antlered game. On the menu, Hi Mountain venison sliders, Susie and Stacy's meatballs, John's mushrooms, Nick Brune's everything salmon and Buddy's little buddy.(n)

programme.title: The Lindsey Way
programme.desc: David and Jeff are doing what they love: bowhunting rutting whitetails. A big cold front moves across the Midwest, and Jeff connects on a rutted-up Iowa bruiser. Kar Franzen wraps his golden Iowa tag around a 180" Iowa booner.(n)

programme.title: Bowlife
programme.desc: It's mid-November and the entire crew is in Kansas with the Evans family. Chris Douglas is coming in to camp hot off a successful hunt and has plans of filming Samantha while Levi wastes no time getting in the tree.(n)

programme.title: Al's Fish'n With Mates
programme.desc: Al McGlashan is on a covert operation as he travels to the top end of Australia to hunt down the million dollar fish. Al explores the Kakadu National Park, dodging crocodiles and sharks just for the shot at a fish of a lifetime.(n)

programme.title: Florida Sportsman Project Dreamboat
programme.desc: The 31' Contender project is on its way to better day, with a fresh non-skid and legendary rigging to come. Also: we put floatation brackets to the test on a 23' Regulator.(n)

programme.title: On the Water with Hank Parker
programme.desc: Hank and Martha Parker host their kids and grandkids for a day of fun in the sun, fishing and fellowship.(n)

programme.title: The Gypsy Angler
programme.desc: Captain Ray Van Horn travels to North Carolina for the annual cobia run.(n)

programme.title: Hook the Future
programme.desc: It's always a good day in Costa Rica. Lucas & Ronald have an epic adventure out of Marina Pez Vela with Jackpot Sport Fishing aboard the Good Day. Captain Ben Gilmore and Captain Don Dingman cheer them on as they battle it out against big mahi.(n)

programme.title: South Walton Fishing Adventures
programme.desc: Join visitors to South Walton, Fla. as they team up with Stinky's Bait Shack to hit the beach to do some surf fishing for pompano. Afterword, the group checks out local dining hot spot, Trebeaché, with their catch where it's cooked up fresh.(n)

programme.title: Emerald Tails
programme.desc: Captain Todd Jones and Captain Jamie Wilkinson looks to mix up a giant bowl of Gulf gumbo with their mix bag of species.(n)

programme.title: Sweetwater
programme.desc: The guys meet up for a family getaway to Big Cedar Lodge on Table Rock Lake. Zeke also joins the fishing action at scenic Dogwood Canyon.(n)

programme.title: Old School Outdoors
programme.desc: Part 1. The Land of Enchantment holds one of the most sought after big game.(n)

programme.title: Dead Meat
programme.desc: Chef Leysath tries to determine if invasive South American rodents can be eaten.(n)

programme.title: Trained Assassins
programme.desc: Part 1. The crew is back chasing rack bucks on their own home turf in Mississippi and Louisiana. They have waited long enough, and now it's time to start laying down some of these southern brutes.(n)

programme.title: The Game Chef
programme.desc: Angelo targets salmon in Lake Hawea, and cooks up a salmon burger with hollandaise, dill and lemon dressing, hot smoked salmon risotto and a salmon omelette with asparagus and tarragon butter.(n)
